---
title: Sandro Petti’s Cheeky Pasta Puttanesca
description: Leave judgment at the door and journey with us to the back streets of 1950’s Naples. A time when men were men and pasta sauces were given particularly risqué names. As legend has it, this dish was created when a restaurant owner called Sandro Petti was closing up for the night and suddenly a group of hungry customers demanded a midnight snack. Petti dove into the kitchen, made up a quick recipe and an Italian classic was born! There are, of course, other versions of the story, but this is a family show!
